<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2010-05-19</DATELINE><TITLE>Feline Lectin Activity Is Critical for the Cellular Entry of Feline Infectious Peritonitis Virus</TITLE><BODY>Feline infectious peritonitis is a lethal disease of felids caused by systemic infection with a feline coronavirus. Here, we report identification and analysis of the feline homologue to the human lectin DC-SIGN and show that it is a coreceptor for virulent strains of serotype 1 and serotype 2 feline coronaviruses.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>